. In dorsal view, distinctly transverse, 1.2–1.4× as wide as long (
<figureCitation id="132C2A1FFFEEFFD0E0C353908C739AE6" box="[984,1067,1505,1531]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11. Coelinius canastra Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 12–14. Coelinius itamonte Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 15–17. Coelinius kali Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 18–20. Coelinius longicephalus sp. nov.; 21–23. Coelinius lux Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 9, 12, 15, 18, 21 head, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 10, 13, 16, 19, 22 head, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 11, 14, 17, 20, 23 mandible, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500719/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), 1.1–1.15× as wide as eye, 1.4× as wide as mesosoma, 1.1–1.3× as wide as long (length of head in lateral view). Shortest distance from occiput to stemmaticum 1.6–1.9× stemmaticum height. Shortest distance from between outer margin of lateral ocellus and margin of eye 1.25–1.5× stemmaticum width. In lateral view, head 1.2–1.35× as long as high (
<figureCitation id="132C2A1FFFEEFFD0E7F9503C8D6F997A" box="[1250,1335,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11. Coelinius canastra Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 12–14. Coelinius itamonte Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 15–17. Coelinius kali Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 18–20. Coelinius longicephalus sp. nov.; 21–23. Coelinius lux Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 9, 12, 15, 18, 21 head, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 10, 13, 16, 19, 22 head, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 11, 14, 17, 20, 23 mandible, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500719/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); temple 1.3–1.7× as long as eye. Eye 0.7–0.9× as long as high. Mandible 2.2–2.4× as long as apical width (
<figureCitation id="132C2A1FFFEEFFD0E7E650008D0A9996" box="[1277,1362,1649,1675]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11. Coelinius canastra Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 12–14. Coelinius itamonte Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 15–17. Coelinius kali Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 18–20. Coelinius longicephalus sp. nov.; 21–23. Coelinius lux Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 9, 12, 15, 18, 21 head, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 10, 13, 16, 19, 22 head, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 11, 14, 17, 20, 23 mandible, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500719/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Face 1.6–2.2× as wide as high, 1.1–1.5× as wide as clypeus, 1.8–2.4× as high as clypeus. Clypeus 2.5–3.3× as wide as high. Paraclypeal fovea minute, occupying 0.4× of the distance from lateral margin of clypeus to eye. Maxillary palp 0.6–0.8× as long as head; third segment 1.25–1.8× as long as fourth. First flagellomere 3.5–4.35× as long as wide, 1.2–1.5× as long as second flagellomere. Second flagellomere 2.9–3.5× as long as wide. Third flagellomere 2.3–2.8× as long as wide. Tenth flagellomere 1.4–1.7× as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEEFFD0E3DC51388C8E987E" blockId="6.[151,1437,1253,2036]" box="[199,1238,1865,1892]" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEEFFD0E3DC51388914987E" bold="true" box="[199,332,1865,1891]" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
2.3–2.7× as long as head (lateral view). Mesoscutum 0.8–0.85× as wide as long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEEFFD0E3DC511C8C8098B1" blockId="6.[151,1437,1253,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEEFFD0E3DC511C895E989A" bold="true" box="[199,262,1901,1927]" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind femur 3.9–4.25× as long as wide. Hind tibia 9.5–10.9× as long as its maximum subapical width, 0.9–1.0× as long as hind tarsus. First segment of hind tarsus 2.0–2.4× as long as second segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEEFFD0E3DC51C48D0398E9" blockId="6.[151,1437,1253,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEEFFD0E3DC51C4896698D2" bold="true" box="[199,318,1973,1999]" pageId="6" pageNumber="205">Fore wing</emphasis>
. 0.6× as long as body. Vein 1-SR+M 0.9–1.0× as long as 2-SR; 2-SR+M 0.2–0.3× as long 2-SR. First subdiscal cell open (CU1b absent); vein cu-a postfurcal, 1.2–1.6× as long as 1-CU1; 2-CU1 0.8–1.05× m-cu.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC56E78A419FE4" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC56E789149FAD" bold="true" box="[199,332,150,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Hind wing.</emphasis>
With three hamuli, 5.1–6.05× as long as wide. Vein 1-M 0.7–0.9× as long as M+CU, 2.8–3.3× as long as 1r-m. Subbasal cell closed. Vein m-cu occasionally present (when present, short and spectral); SR and 2-M heavily pigmented but not tubular.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC577289F69E5C" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC577289139E00" bold="true" box="[199,331,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Metasoma.</emphasis>
1.3–1.4× as long as head plus mesosoma length. First metasomal tergite with apex 1.7–1.8× as wide as base; dorsope present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC573A8B659D04" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC573A895C9E78" bold="true" box="[199,260,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Male</emphasis>
. Shortest distance from occiput to stemmaticum 1.5–1.8× stemmaticum height. Shortest distance from between outer margin of lateral ocellus and margin of eye 1.2–1.35× stemmaticum width. Paraclypeal fovea occupying 0.5× of the distance from lateral margin of clypeus to eye. Face 2.0–2.4× as wide as high. Second flagellomere 2.8–3.2× as long as wide. Tenth flagellomere 1.7–2.0× as long as wide. Fore wing with vein 1-SR+M 1.0–1.1× as long as 2-SR. Hind wing with vein 1-M 0.6–0.85× as long as M+CU, 2.85–4.0× as long as 1r-m. Metasoma 1.45–1.5× as long as head plus mesosoma length.
</paragraph>
